    "ITS PARKA TIME AGAIN PLACE YOUR ORDERS NOW For MadetoOrder FUR OR CLOTH PARKAS Alpaca and Milium Lined for Extra Warmth for the Cold Windy Days Coming Soon Also MUKLUCKS AND MITTS FOR THE WHOLE FAMILY UAW Signs 3Year j Contract With Ford DETROIT AThe Ford Motor Co looked hopefully forward to a period of labor peace based on a new threeyear agreement with the United Auto Workers Union The pact is expected to set a pat tern for the entire auto industry Ford and the UAW announced a settlement of their differences Wednesday several hours after some 98000 workers walked off their jobs in Ford plants across the nation The strike remained in effect at some plants pending agreement on local problems With the Ford contract tucked in his pocket UAW president Wal ter Reufher said he will now turn his attention to General Motors j and Chrysler He undoubtedly will ask for similar contract gains from the two firms Terms of the Ford pact which must still be ratified and ap proved by UAW locals bring an approximate 10 cen hourly pay raise for all workers plus extra fringe benefits The new average hourly rate is estimated at"
